  "body": "Geth version: 1.8.15-stable (the armhf distribution)\r\nOS & Version: Linux Raspbian v9 (Stretch)\r\nKernel Linux raspberrypi 4.14.69-v7+ #1141 SMP Mon Sep 10 15:26:29 BST 2018 armv7l GNU/Linux\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nNot to lock up the whole Pi\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAfter about 9 hours, performance of the Pi tails off to the point where the mouse pointer is stuck, and ^C will no longer safely shut down the geth application.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nPi version 3B+\r\nFarnell Pi Desktop with Kingston 120GB SSD\r\n8G swap on /dev/sda2\r\nThe rest is data on /dev/sda1\r\n\r\nsudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/eth\r\nsudo swapon /dev/sda2\r\nsudo swapoff /var/swap\r\n/mnt/eth/geth --datadir /mnt/eth/data 2>>~/geth.log\r\nin another terminal window, tail -f geth.log\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\nSince the 3B+ has only 1G of physical RAM, swap is necessary.\r\nSwap is only on the (relatively) fast SSD on the desktop hat, instead of the slow SD card.\r\nTemperature isn't a concern, as long as I run it with the lid off, so no CPU throttling.\r\nThe default cache=2048 is automatically reset during geth starup to 291.",
